My vim config files

Installation:

    git clone git@github.com:trevormorse/vimfiles.git ~/.vim

Create symlinks:

    ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

    cd ~/.vim
    git submodule init
    git submodule update

If you want to use vim-task you'll need to do this:

    cd ~/.vim
    mkdir ftdetect
    ln -s ~/.vim/bundle/vim-task/ftdetect/task.vim ftdetect/task.vim
